unloadPtnPin(25.10)                                        unloadPtnPin(25.10)

Name
       unloadPtnPin  - Removes the loading of partition pins by the loadPtnPin
       command

Syntax
       unloadPtnPin

       [-help]

       -ptnName <partitionName>

       {-file <floorplanFileName> }

       Removes the loading of partition pins by the loadPtnPin  command.  This
       is  used to remove the preassignment of pins that were previously reas-
       signed by the loading.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each unloadPtnPin parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man unloadPtnPin

       -file <floorplanFileName>
              Specifies the full pathname of the partition floorplan file.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -ptnName <partitionName>
              Specifies the name of the partition.

              Data_type: string, required

Example
       The following command unloads pin positions for partition EUG from file
       EUG.fp.ptn:

       unloadPtnPin -ptnName EUG -file EUG.fp.ptn

